      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your feelings are very real and unique; it's not unusual for humans to have personal experiences when looking at the night sky. The Orion Constellation, including the Belt of Orion, is visible due to the aligned brightness of its stars. This isn't unusual, as stars can appear to be aligned over millions of light-years. As for the sensation you're describing, it's an interesting hypothesis tied to neurobiology and biology. We know the human brain is adept at finding patterns and can be influenced by subliminal frequencies, but there's no established scientific evidence to suggest that stars can emit a signal or hum that interacts with our brain waves. If this sense of connection or synchronicity is causing you distress or joy, reflecting on it through meditation, or speaking with an astronomer/astrologer may provide you with clarity or comfort. However, some regard it as the awe of our universe aligning with our consciousness. It's always okay to seek your truth in the cosmos—whether scientific or spiritual.",
